snippet: The House will not have time to vote on a bill until early next year, Representative Kevin McCarthy, the majority whip, told protesters in his California district.
abstract: Rep Kevin McCarthy, top Republican lawmaker and majority whip, tells protesters he met in his California district that the House of Representatives will not have time to vote on any immigration measure until early in 2014.
lead_paragraph: The House will not have time to vote on a bill until early next year, Representative Kevin McCarthy, the majority whip, told protesters in his California district.

headline.main: Immigration Vote Unlikely This Year, Lawmaker Says
headline.print_headline: Immigration Vote Unlikely This Year, Lawmaker Says
